Name: SP
Content:
If you're depending on a NIFTY-50 SIP for a 12% annual return to reach your financial goal, historically, the probability of achieving this goal has been roughly 50%
the same as the probability of getting a toss of a coin right!

Name: SP
Content:
What are the implications of this?
Suppose you have a financial goal set for a 5-year horizon, like establishing a college fund for your child who is currently in the seventh grade. Your strategy involves relying on a 5-year SIP in the NIFTY-50 to generate a 12% annual return.

Name: SP
Content:
In the series opener, I delve into the historical odds of attaining a low double digit (11%-12% pa) return via a 5-year SIP in the NIFTY-50.
 Spoiler alert: Historically, the chance of achieving a 12%+ annual return in a 5-year NIFTY-50 SIP is as low as flipping a coin (50%).
